====Usage notes====
Some authorities, chiefly in the UK, suggest that the plural of ''trade union'' is {{m|en|trade unions}} when the relevant unions all represent the same trade (for example, "''The train drivers were divided between two '''trade unions'''.''"), but {{m|en|trades unions}} when they represent different trades (for example, "''There are hundreds of '''trades unions''' in England.''"). However, {{m|en|trade unions}} is commonly used for both cases.<ref>'''2011''', Simon Heffer, ''Simply English: An A-Z of Avoidable Errors'', page 359</ref>

